"We present an algorithm to compute the zeta function of an arbitrary hyperelliptic curve over a finite field Fq of characteristic 2, thereby extending the algorithm of Kedlaya for odd characteristic. Given a genus g hyperelliptic curve defined over Fqn, the average-case time complexity is O(g4 + e n3 + e) and the average-case space complexity is O(g3 n3), whereas the worst-case time and space complexities are O(g5 + e n3 + e) and O(g4 n3), respectively."
